Verdict: MAJOR

Findings by severity:

MAJOR: HTML artifact still documents the old placeholder OCIMF equations. In `_html_report()` method/provenance text, the generated HTML still says `Cx=1.05*abs(cos(ψ)); Cy=sin(ψ); Cm=0.55*sin(ψ)`. That directly contradicts the #2760 workbook-derived OCIMF requirement and would leave a false provenance trail even if calculation-time code uses the workbook.

MAJOR: The generated HTML has stale default-rudder contract text. Chart 1 says “All 21 rudder angles are selectable; the default rudder angle is neutral 0.0 deg,” but #2760 requires rudder 0..28 deg in 2 deg increments, default 28 deg. The selector appears to default to 28, but the artifact text is wrong and should not be committed as the engineer-facing package.

MAJOR: The implementation still presents horizontal resultants under renamed labels. `_row()` computes `math.hypot(...)` fields as `*_component_horizontal_force_N`, and the selected-case breakdown shows them as “Component check (kN)”. That is still a horizontal resultant, just renamed. Since #2760 explicitly says to remove the prior resultant presentation as the main package and keep X/Y/N component comparisons side-by-side, this should either be removed from the main report/table or clearly moved out of the main comparison path.

MINOR: Chart/report narrative is internally inconsistent. Markdown says Chart 2 overlays OCIMF current-review, rudder, and total yaw moment, but the HTML Chart 2 is only rudder-induced yaw moment, while Chart 4 is the OCIMF/rudder/total yaw comparison. This weakens artifact coherence.

MINOR: Tests do catch removal of the old constants/formulas by source-string checks, but the workbook coefficient regression is narrow. A hardcoded implementation for the tested 175-degree point could pass. Add at least one more heading/sign case, preferably negative heading and centerline, and assert workbook provenance/source is reflected in output artifacts.

Answering the review questions: calculation-time code does appear to route through `resolve_ocimf_loaded_tanker_current_coefficients()` and fail closed on missing workbook/provenance, but the generated HTML provenance still advertises the old formulas. Tests are directionally good, but they missed stale HTML method text, stale default-rudder copy, and disguised resultant presentation. I would not approve commit/close until those artifact-contract defects are fixed.
